The ANC’s Eastern Cape provincial conference kicks off on Friday. This after multiple attempts to halt it. Treasurer General Paul Mashatile met with the provincial leadership yesterday. eNCA speaks to political analyst, Lukhanyo Vangqa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC’s Eastern Cape provincial conference kicks off on Friday. This comes after multiple attempts to halt it. READ: Eastern Cape ANC calls for calm after members gunned down Treasurer General Paul Mashatile met with the provincial leadership on Thursday and gave the green light to two contenders for leadership positions to participate in the conference. Earlier this week two Nelson Mandela Bay ANC members were killed. The two murders were after another ANC councillor Zwelandile Booi was gunned down in February. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more details. Courtesy #DStv403